Dear Comrade, I am Chris Tang Ping-keung, Commissioner of Police. Today is hard work for everyone. Although there are colleagues who want to deal with the scene in Mong Kok, overall, our early intervention and decisive enforcement strategies are very effective. Your professional performance has made people who want to go back to work today want to go back to school very smoothly, and the Legislative Council can also hold meetings without interference. In fact, the rioters wanted to make a comeback from the Sunday just past all the way today, but what do they do is destined to be in vain, what do you think? Because Hong Kong has our own class, the good police guard Hong Kong day and night. In the past few days, I have been on a good meal like everyone, and I am fully committed to the action of the wave-walker again. Although everyone may seem to have less training and more work than returning to the house, but every time I see My colleagues are all energetic, and I know that the morale of the domestic police force is very high. In the past year, we have been striving for self-improvement. From intelligence, investigation, equipment, training to the implementation of tactics, we have continuously made progress and become more determined to be passive. Even though the rioters thought it was possible to block the road and make chaos, we have already taken the initiative to strategize and arrest multiple rioters. We also arrest rioters who tried to block the Cross Habour Tunnel. At noon, some people went to Central, Causeway Bay and Mong Kok to disrupt the social order, and we did not hesitate to make an arrest. The efficiency of your actions today is obvious to all. Everyone will not be wasted in every drop of sweat left under the high temperature of 30 degree celsius. The efforts you have made for Hong Kong have made the unruly rioters already very small. At the same time, it also provides energy to the society. Sun Tzu's art of war mentioned: &quot;Triumph Comes When Leaders and Followers Share the Same Goal&quot; means that we are united, and we will definitely win. The success of today &rsquo;s operation is precisely due to the unity of the police force, fighting for the common goal of restoring social order in Hong Kong. In the future, we will still face many challenges, but I have great confidence. Because the unity and ability of the police force are unprecedented today, the police force will drive away the darkness for Hong Kong and the brighter the day, the closer Thank you all. OUT &quot;

